{"title_page": "List of awards and nominations received by Irrfan Khan", "text_new": "{{Use Indian English|date=November 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}}\n{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{Infobox actor awards\n|name=Irrfan Khan\n|image=Irrfan Khan still5.jpg\n|caption=Khan at the premiere of ''The Namesake''\n|wins=32\n|nominations=34\n|collapse=yes\n|award1=[[Filmfare Awards]]\n|award1W=4\n|award1N=2\n|award2=[[Zee Cine Awards]]\n|award2W=0\n|award2N=5\n|award3=[[Screen Awards]]\n|award3W=4\n|award3N=4\n|award4=[[Stardust Awards]] \n|award4W=1\n|award4N=2\n|award5=[[Producers Guild Film Awards]]\n|award5W=2\n|award5N=7\n|award6=[[IIFA Awards]]\n|award6W=3\n|award6N=5\n|award7=[[National Film Awards]]\n|award7W=1\n|award7N=0\n|award8=[[Big Star Entertainment Awards]]\n|award8W=0\n|award8N=2\n|award9=Other awards\n|award9W=12\n|award9N=7\n|award10=Honours\n|award10W=5\n|award10N=0\n}}\n'''[[Irrfan Khan|S\u0101hibz\u0101de Irfan Ali Khan]]''' (7 January 1967{{en dash}}29 April 2020), also credited as simply '''Irrfan''', was an [[Indian film]] actor, known for his work predominantly in [[Hindi cinema]], as well as his works in [[Cinema of the United Kingdom|British films]] and [[Hollywood]].<ref name=\"Irrfan drops Khan\">{{cite web |url=http://news.avstv.com/2012/03/07/irrfan-drops-khan/ |title=Irfan drops 'Khan{{'-}} |publisher=News.avstv.com |accessdate=2012-07-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927162036/http://news.avstv.com/2012/03/07/irrfan-drops-khan/ |archivedate=27 September 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Jha |first=Subhash K |url=http://www.mid-day.com/entertainment/2012/mar/070312-Irrfan-drops-his-surname-Khan.htm |title=Irrfan drops his surname Khan |publisher=Mid-day.com |date=7 March 2012 |accessdate=2012-07-21}}</ref> He was form jaipur , a district in rajasthan .in childhood he wants to be a cricketer , and also he got selected in district team but than due to lack of money irrfan dropped the plan of be a cricketer because he can't able to afford 600\u20b9 per month . so he choose his another Love cinema.\n\nIn a film career spanning almost thirty years and featuring in more than fifty domestic films, Khan has received numerous awards, including a [[National Film Awards|National Film Award]] and [[Filmfare Awards]] in four categories. Film critics, contemporaries and other experts consider him to be one of the finest actors in [[Cinema of India|Indian cinema]] for his versatile and natural acting.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jurassic-world-actor-irrfan-khan-756206|title='Jurassic World' Actor Irfan Khan on Upcoming Film: \"It Will Be Like a Scary Adventure\"|first1=Ariston|last1=Anderson|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=10 December 2014|accessdate=28 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2013/jul/25/irrfan-khan-bollywood-d-day|title=Irrfan Khan: 'I object to the term Bollywood'|first1=Nosheen|last1=Iqbal|work=the Guardian|date=25 July 2013|accessdate=28 October 2015}}</ref> In 2011, he was awarded the [[Padma Shri]], India's fourth highest civilian honour for his contribution to the field of arts.<ref name=\"Padma Awards\">{{cite web|url=http://mha.nic.in/sites/upload_files/mha/files/LST-PDAWD-2013.pdf |title=Padma Awards |publisher=Ministry of Home Affairs, Government of India |date=2015 |accessdate=21 July 2015 |format=PDF |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6U68ulwpb?url=http://mha.nic.in/sites/upload_files/mha/files/LST-PDAWD-2013.pdf |archivedate=15 November 2014 }}</ref>\n\nDomestically, he made his screen debut with the [[Academy Awards|Academy Award]] nominated film ''[[Salaam Bombay!]]'' (1988). Followed by a series of roles in films that failed to propel his career forward, he received critical acclaim for playing negative roles in the [[Drama Film|drama]] films ''[[Haasil]]'' (2003) and ''[[Maqbool]]'' (2004), for the former he won the [[Filmfare Award for Best Performance in a Negative Role|Filmfare Award for Best Villain]]. The successful drama ''[[Life in a... Metro]]'' (2007) marked a turning point in Khan's career, earning him praise and several awards including the [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor]]. He rose to prominence with his portrayal of [[Paan Singh Tomar]] in the acclaimed [[Biographical film|biographical]] sports drama ''[[Paan Singh Tomar (film)|Paan Singh Tomar]]'' (2011), which garnered him the [[National Film Award for Best Actor]] and a [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actor]].<ref name=\"60thaward\">{{cite press_release |title=60th National Film Awards Announced |url=http://pib.nic.in/archieve/others/2013/mar/d2013031801.pdf |format=PDF |publisher=Press Information Bureau (PIB), India |accessdate=18 March 2013}}</ref> His performance in the [[British Academy of Film and Television Arts|BAFTA Award]] nominated romance ''[[The Lunchbox]]'' (2013) earned him universal acclaim by the critics and audiences. Khan went on to feature in the commercially and critically successful films ''[[Haider (film)|Haider]]'' (2014), ''[[Gunday]]'' (2014), ''[[Piku]]'' (2015) and ''[[Talvar (film)|Talvar]]'' (2015). His highest-grossing Hindi release came with the critically acclaimed [[comedy-drama]] ''[[Hindi Medium]]'' (2017), which became a sleeper hit in [[India]] and [[China]], which ranks among [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing Indian films of all time]] and earned him praise for his performance, winning several awards including the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor]].\n[[File:The President, Smt. Pratibha Devisingh Patil presenting the Padma Shri Award to Shri Sahabzade Irrfan Ali Khan, at an Investiture Ceremony II, at Rashtrapati Bhavan, in New Delhi on April 01, 2011.jpg|thumb|250px|Khan received [[Padma Shri]] award from former Indian president [[Pratibha Patil]] in 2011]]\n\n==Awards and honours==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Film\n!Award\n!Category\