ds East]]\n| Critics\u2019 Award for Best Actor (Male)\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.filmfare.com/features/nominations-for-the-jio-filmfare-awards-east-2018_-26583-2.html|title=Nominations for the Jio Filmfare Awards (East) 2018|work=filmfare.com|access-date=2018-02-14|language=en}}</ref>\n|}\n==See also==\n* [[List of accolades received by Slumdog Millionaire]]\n* [[List of accolades received by Piku]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDB name|451234|Irrfan Khan|section=Awards}}\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Khan, Irrfan}}\n[[Category:Bollywood lists of awards and nominations]]\n[[Category:Lists of awards received by actor]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Indian English|date=November 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}}\n{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{Infobox actor awards\n|name=Irrfan Khan\n|image=Irrfan Khan still5.jpg\n|caption=Khan at the premiere of ''The Namesake''\n|wins=32\n|nominations=34\n|collapse=yes\n|award1=[[Filmfare Awards]]\n|award1W=4\n|award1N=2\n|award2=[[Zee Cine Awards]]\n|award2W=0\n|award2N=5\n|award3=[[Screen Awards]]\n|award3W=4\n|award3N=4\n|award4=[[Stardust Awards]] \n|award4W=1\n|award4N=2\n|award5=[[Producers Guild Film Awards]]\n|award5W=2\n|award5N=7\n|award6=[[IIFA Awards]]\n|award6W=3\n|award6N=5\n|award7=[[National Film Awards]]\n|award7W=1\n|award7N=0\n|award8=[[Big Star Entertainment Awards]]\n|award8W=0\n|award8N=2\n|award9=Other awards\n|award9W=12\n|award9N=7\n|award10=Honours\n|award10W=5\n|award10N=0\n}}\n'''[[Irrfan Khan|S\u0101hibz\u0101de Irfan Ali Khan]]''' (7 January 1967{{en dash}}29 April 2020), also credited as simply '''Irrfan''', was an [[Indian film]] actor, known for his work predominantly in [[Hindi cinema]], as well as his works in [[Cinema of the United Kingdom|British films]] and [[Hollywood]].<ref name=\"Irrfan drops Khan\">{{cite web |url=http://news.avstv.com/2012/03/07/irrfan-drops-khan/ |title=Irfan drops 'Khan{{'-}} |publisher=News.avstv.com |accessdate=2012-07-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927162036/http://news.avstv.com/2012/03/07/irrfan-drops-khan/ |archivedate=27 September 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Jha |first=Subhash K |url=http://www.mid-day.com/entertainment/2012/mar/070312-Irrfan-drops-his-surname-Khan.htm |title=Irrfan drops his surname Khan |publisher=Mid-day.com |date=7 March 2012 |accessdate=2012-07-21}}</ref> In a film career spanning almost thirty years and featuring in more than fifty domestic films, Khan has received numerous awards, including a [[National Film Awards|National Film Award]] and [[Filmfare Awards]] in four categories. Film critics, contemporaries and other experts consider him to be one of the finest actors in [[Cinema of India|Indian cinema]] for his versatile and natural acting.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jurassic-world-actor-irrfan-khan-756206|title='Jurassic World' Actor Irfan Khan on Upcoming Film: \"It Will Be Like a Scary Adventure\"|first1=Ariston|last1=Anderson|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=10 December 2014|accessdate=28 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2013/jul/25/irrfan-khan-bollywood-d-day|title=Irrfan Khan: 'I object to the term Bollywood'|first1=Nosheen|last1=Iqbal|work=the Guardian|date=25 July 2013|accessdate=28 October 2015}}</ref> In 2011, he was awarded the [[Padma Shri]], India's fourth highest civilian honour for his contribution to the field of arts.<ref name=\"Padma Awards\">{{cite web|url=http://mha.nic.in/sites/upload_files/mha/files/LST-PDAWD-2013.pdf |title=Padma Awards |publisher=Ministry of Home Affairs, Government of India |date=2015 |accessdate=21 July 2015 |format=PDF |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6U68ulwpb?url=http://mha.nic.in/sites/upload_files/mha/files/LST-PDAWD-2013.pdf |archivedate=15 November 2014 }}</ref>\n\nDomestically, he made his screen debut with the [[Academy Awards|Academy Award]] nominated film ''[[Salaam Bombay!]]'' (1988). Followed by a series of roles in films that failed to propel his career forward, he received critical acclaim for playing negative roles in the [[Drama Film|drama]] films ''[[Haasil]]'' (2003) and ''[[Maqbool]]'' (2004), for the former he won the [[Filmfare Award for Best Performance in a Negative Role|Filmfare Award for Best Villain]]. The successful drama ''[[Life in a... Metro]]'' (2007) marked a turning point in Khan's career, earning him praise and several awards including the [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor]]. He rose to prominence with his portrayal of [[Paan Singh Tomar]] in the acclaimed [[Biographical film|biographical]] sports drama ''[[Paan Singh Tomar (film)|Paan Singh Tomar]]'' (2011), which garnered him the [[National Film Award for Best Actor]] and a [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actor]].<ref name=\"60thaward\">{{cite press_release |title=60th National Film Awards Announced |url=http://pib.nic.in/archieve/others/2013/mar/d2013031801.pdf |format=PDF |publisher=Press Information Bureau (PIB), India |accessdate=18 March 2013}}</ref> His performance in the [[British Academy of Film and Television Arts|BAFTA Award]] nominated romance ''[[The Lunchbox]]'' (2013) earned him universal acclaim by the critics and audiences. Khan went on to feature in the commercially and critically successful films ''[[Haider (film)|Haider]]'' (2014), ''[[Gunday]]'' (2014), ''[[Piku]]'' (2015) and ''[[Talvar (film)|Talvar]]'' (2015). His highest-grossing Hindi release came with the critically acclaimed [[comedy-drama]] ''[[Hindi Medium]]'' (2017), which became a sleeper hit in [[India]] and [[China]], which ranks among [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing Indian films of all time]] and earned him praise for his performance, winning several awards including the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor]].\n[[File:The President, Smt. Pratibha Devisingh Patil presenting the Padma Shri Award to Shri Sahabzade Irrfan Ali Khan, at an Investiture Ceremony II, at Rashtrapati Bhavan, in New Delhi on April 01, 2011.jpg|thumb|250px|Khan received [[Padma Shri]] award from former Indian president [[Pratibha Patil]] in 2011]]\n\n==Awards and honours==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Film\n!Award\n!Category\n!Result\n!Ref.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" |2004\n| rowspan=\"3\" |''[[Haasil]]''\n|[[Filmfare Awards]]\n|Best Actor in a Negative Role\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Zee Cine Awards]]\n|Best Performance in a Villainous Role\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Screen Awards]]\n|Best Performance in a Negative Role\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''[[Maqbool]]''\n|Best Performance in a Negative Role\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Zee Cine Awards]]\n|Best Performance in a Villainous Role\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n|2007\n| rowspan=\"3\" |''[[The Namesake (film)|The Namesake]]''\n|[[Alliance of Women Film Journalists]]\n|Best Seduction\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2007\n|[[Independent Spirit Award]]\n|Best Supporting Male\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Stardust Awards]]\n|Best Supporting Actor\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" |''[[Life in a... Metro]]''\n|[[Producers Guild Film Awards]]\n|Best Actor in a Supporting Role\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" |2008\n|[[Filmfare Awards]]\n|Best Supporting Actor\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[International Indian Film Academy Awards]]\n|Best Supporting Actor\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|Best Performance in a Comic Role\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" | [[Screen Awards]]\n|Best Comedian\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|Best Supporting Actor\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''[[Slumdog Millionaire]]''\n|[[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Cast in a Motion Picture|Screen Actors Guild Award]]\n|[[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Cast in a Motion Picture|Outstanding Performance by a Cast in a Motion Picture]]\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2009\n|Central Ohio Film Critics Association\n|Best Ensemble\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|''[[Mumbai Meri Jaan]]''\n|[[International Indian Film Academy Awards]]\n|Best Actor In A Supporting Role\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n|{{N/a}}\n|[[GQ (Indian edition)]]\n|Man of the Year\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2010\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''[[New York (2009 film)|New York]]''\n|[[Producers Guild Film Awards]]\n|Best Actor In A Supporting Role\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n|[[International Indian Film Academy Awards]]\n|Best Actor In A Supporting Role\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2011\n|{{N/a}}\n|[[Padma Shri]]\n|Arts\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|{{N/a}}\n|[[International Indian Film Academy Awards]]\n|[[12th IIFA Awards|Outstanding Achievement in International Cinema]]\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2012\n|{{N/a}}\n|[[CNN-IBN Indian of the Year]]\n|Entertainment\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|''[[7 Khoon Maaf]]''\n|[[International Indian Film Academy Awards]]\n|Best Performance in a Negative Role\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"13\" |2013\n| rowspan=\"8\" |''[[Paan Singh Tomar (film)|Paan Singh Tomar]]''\n|[[National Film Awards]]\n|Best Actor\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Filmfare Awards]]\n|Best Actor\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n|Best Actor (Critics)\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Producers Guild Film Awards]]\n|Best Actor\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Zee Cine Awards]]\n|Best Actor\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Times of India Film Awards]]\n|Best Actor\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|Institute for Research and Documentation in Social Sciences\n|Best Male Character\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Screen Awards]]\n|Best Actor\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"8\" |''[[The Lunchbox]]''\n|Best Actor\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Asian Film Awards]]\n|Best Actor\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Asia-Pacific Film Festival]]\n|Outstanding Achievement Award\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|Best Actor\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Dubai International Film Festival]]\n|Best Actor\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" |2014\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Producers Guild Film Awards]]\n|Best Actor\n|{{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n|Star Verdict Performer of the Year\n|{{Won}}\n|\n|-\n|Entertainer of the Year\n|{{Won}}